PDB VIEWER INTERFACE OVERVIEW:

	PDB Viewer:
	
	Proteins -a sub menu containing pre defined structures
		  (configured in config.xml see below)

	Protein Morphs - a sub menu containing pre defined protein
		  morphs (configured in config.xml see below)

	Loader - a loader for individual structures, dial in the four
		  digit/Alpha PDB ID then load to load the structure

	Protein Fader - a sub menu containing controls to the protein
		  fader

		  Fade On - enables the fader, it will override
			High Detail mode

		  Distance from viewer (mtr) - Indicates the distance
			from the viewer, where the fade will begin

		  Fade distance (mtr) - Indicates the size of the faded
			section 
			e.g. settings 1, 1: fade would occur in the 
			interval 1-2 meters away from the viewer

		  Reset Settings - Resets the Distance from viewer and
			Fade distance settings
			(configured in config.xml see below)
			 
	High Detail - Enables/disables two different representations of
		  the loaded structure

	Clear - removes currently structures from the enviroment



Example PDBPlugin configuartion in the config.xml:

  <PDBPlugin>
        <PDBPluginMolDir value="/home/johndoe/covise/src/renderer/OpenCOVER/plugins/PDBPlugin/" />
        <PDBUrl value="www.pdb.org/pdb/files/" />
        <AnimationURL value="www.molmovdb.org/uploads/" />
        <ViewerDistance value="1.1" />
        <FadeDistance value="1.2" />
        <Structures>
          Myoglobin 1MBN
          DNA 1BNA
          Photosystem_I 1JBO
          Cytochrome_c_Oxidase 1OCO
          Collagen 1CAG
          MHC_Class_II 1DLH
          Potassium_Channel_A 1BL8
          Potassium_Channel_B 1FQY
          SARS 2D2D
          Glutamate_Receptor 1GR2
          Acetylcholine_Receptor 2BG9
          Acetylcholine_Cobratoxin 1YI5
          Thermus_Thermophilus 1J5E
        </Structures>
        <Animations>
          Serotonin_N-Acetyltransferase 22943-38
          Calcium_Pump 396506-12995
          FecA_transporter 829808-15750
          Actin 763408-1487
          Calmodulin 17833-29779
        </Animations>
  </PDBPlugin>

	

